In the first place the blue of heaven is shaken with thunder, because the ethereal clouds clash together as they fly aloft when the winds combat from opposite quarters. For no sound ever comes from a clondssess part of heaven, but wheresoever the clouds are gathered in a denser mass, from that part with greater fre- quency comes a clap with a loud growl.
